#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.36"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.36:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga "
msgstr "4. Situations "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.36:0.3"
msgid "36. Doṇasutta "
msgstr "36. Doṇa "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.38, sc1
msgctxt "an4.36:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā antarā ca ukkaṭṭhaṃ antarā ca setabyaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was traveling along the road between Ukkaṭṭhā and Setabya, "

msgctxt "an4.36:1.2"
msgid "Doṇopi sudaṃ brāhmaṇo antarā ca ukkaṭṭhaṃ antarā ca setabyaṃ addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti. "
msgstr "as was the brahmin Doṇa. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:1.3"
msgid "Addasā kho doṇo brāhmaṇo bhagavato pādesu cakkāni sahassārāni sanemikāni sanābhikāni sabbākāraparipūrāni; "
msgstr "Doṇa saw that the Buddha’s footprints had thousand-spoked wheels, with rims and hubs, complete in every detail. "

msgctxt "an4.36:1.4"
msgid "disvānassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "It occurred to him, "

msgctxt "an4.36:1.5"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho. "
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing! "

msgctxt "an4.36:1.6"
msgid "Na vatimāni manussabhūtassa padāni bhavissantī”ti. "
msgstr "Surely these couldn’t be the footprints of a human being?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:1.7"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā maggā okkamma aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisīdi pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā. "
msgstr "The Buddha had left the road and sat at the root of a tree cross-legged, with his body straight and his mindfulness established right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: saṃyatindriyaṃ → yatindriyaṃ (s1) | santindriyaṃ (s2, s3, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.36:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho doṇo brāhmaṇo bhagavato padāni anugacchanto addasa bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinnaṃ pāsādikaṃ pasādanīyaṃ santindriyaṃ santamānasaṃ uttamadamathasamathamanuppattaṃ dantaṃ guttaṃ saṃyatindriyaṃ nāgaṃ. "
msgstr "Then Doṇa, following the Buddha’s footprints, saw him sitting at the tree root—impressive and inspiring, with peaceful faculties and mind, attained to the highest taming and serenity, like an elephant with tamed, guarded, and controlled faculties. "

msgctxt "an4.36:1.9"
msgid "Disvāna yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He went up to the Buddha and said to him: "

# NOTE: For this use of the future tense, cp. kimevidaṃ bhavissati in DN 27
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.36:2.1"
msgid "“Devo no bhavaṃ bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, might you be a god?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.2"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, devo bhavissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will not be a god, brahmin.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.3"
msgid "“Gandhabbo no bhavaṃ bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Might you be a fairy?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.4"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, gandhabbo bhavissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will not be a fairy.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.5"
msgid "“Yakkho no bhavaṃ bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Might you be a native spirit?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.6"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yakkho bhavissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will not be a native spirit.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.7"
msgid "“Manusso no bhavaṃ bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "“Might you be a human?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:2.8"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, manusso bhavissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will not be a human.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.36:3.1"
msgid "“‘Devo no bhavaṃ bhavissatī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr "“When asked whether you might be a god, fairy, native spirit, or human, "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.2"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, devo bhavissāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr "you answer that you will not be any of these. "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.3"
msgid "‘Gandhabbo no bhavaṃ bhavissatī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.4"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, gandhabbo bhavissāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.5"
msgid "‘Yakkho no bhavaṃ bhavissatī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.6"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, yakkho bhavissāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.7"
msgid "‘Manusso no bhavaṃ bhavissatī’ti, iti puṭṭho samāno: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.8"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, manusso bhavissāmī’ti vadesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an4.36:3.9"
msgid "Atha ko carahi bhavaṃ bhavissatī”ti? "
msgstr "What then might you be?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.39, sc4
msgctxt "an4.36:4.1"
msgid "“Yesaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, āsavānaṃ appahīnattā devo bhaveyyaṃ, te me āsavā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr "“Brahmin, if I had not given up defilements I might have become a god … a fairy … a native spirit … or a human. But I have given up those defilements, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, obliterated them so they are unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "an4.36:4.2"
msgid "Yesaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, āsavānaṃ appahīnattā gandhabbo bhaveyyaṃ … yakkho bhaveyyaṃ … manusso bhaveyyaṃ, te me āsavā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:4.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, uppalaṃ vā padumaṃ vā puṇḍarīkaṃ vā udake jātaṃ udake saṃvaḍḍhaṃ udakā accuggamma tiṭṭhati anupalittaṃ udakena; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a blue water lily, or a pink or white lotus. Though it sprouted and grew in the water, it would rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to it. "

msgctxt "an4.36:4.4"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, loke jāto loke saṃvaḍḍho lokaṃ abhibhuyya viharāmi anupalitto lokena. "
msgstr "In the same way, though I was born and grew up in the world, I live having mastered the world, and the world does not cling to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.36:4.5"
msgid "Buddhoti maṃ, brāhmaṇa, dhārehīti. "
msgstr "Remember me, brahmin, as a Buddha. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.36:5.1"
msgid "Yena devūpapatyassa, "
msgstr "I could have been reborn as a god, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.36:5.2"
msgid "gandhabbo vā vihaṅgamo; "
msgstr "or as a fairy flying through the sky. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.36:5.3"
msgid "Yakkhattaṃ yena gaccheyyaṃ, "
msgstr "I could have become a native spirit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.36:5.4"
msgid "manussattañca abbaje; "
msgstr "or returned as a human. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.36:5.5"
msgid "Te mayhaṃ āsavā khīṇā, "
msgstr "But the defilements that could bring about these rebirths "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.36:5.6"
msgid "viddhastā vinaḷīkatā. "
msgstr "I’ve ended, smashed, and gutted. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.36:6.1"
msgid "Puṇḍarīkaṃ yathā vaggu, "
msgstr "Like a graceful lotus, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Toyena nupalippati → toye na upalippati (pts1) | toyena nupalimpati (mr)
msgctxt "an4.36:6.2"
msgid "Toyena nupalippati; "
msgstr "to which water does not cling, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Nupalippāmi → nupalittomhi (bj) | na upalippāmi (pts1) | nupalimpāmi (mr)
msgctxt "an4.36:6.3"
msgid "Nupalippāmi lokena, "
msgstr "the world doesn’t cling to me, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.36:6.4"
msgid "Tasmā buddhosmi brāhmaṇā”ti. "
msgstr "and so, brahmin, I am a Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.36:6.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
